## Debugging "File Not Found" Error

The error accessing the catalog page is likely due to:
1.  **Missing Template:** There is no `page-catalogo.php` in your child theme. WordPress falls back to [archive-product.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/koby/wp-content/themes/rappod/woocommerce/archive-product.php) (parent theme).
2.  **Hardcoded Redirect:** Your [functions.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/koby/wp-content/themes/rappod/functions.php) redirects users to `/catalogo/`. If the page slug is actually `tienda` or [shop](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/koby/wp-content/themes/rappod-child/functions.php#72-79), this leads to a 404.
3.  **Permalinks:** The rewrite rules might need flushing (Settings > Permalinks > Save).

**Action:** We will verify the redirect logic and ensure the shortcode works regardless of the page slug.

